'''The Rock Across Australia''', or "TRAA", is a compilation of weekly Christian charts according to the number of radio plays in [[Australia]]. It published its first report on 15 February 1999 and has been serving the Christian music community and Christian radio sector ever since. The chart listed the top&nbsp;30 most played songs.<ref name="Eliezer"/> It named Michael W Smith as Artist of the Year for 2002 and his track, "Purified", as Song of the Year.<ref name="Mark">{{cite web | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/79262/20071115-0931/jmm.aaa.net.au/articles/8737.html | url = http://jmm.aaa.net.au/articles/8737.html | title = 2002's Artist and Song of the Year | publisher = John Mark Ministries | archivedate = 15 November 2007 | date = 6 January 2003 | accessdate = 23 December 2015 }}</ref> In March 2009 TRAA's researcher was Wes Jay.<ref name="Eliezer">{{cite web | archiveurl = http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/10761/20100218-0125/www.themusic.com.au/imm_display6fb2.html | url = http://www.themusic.com.au/imm_display6fb2.html | title = Sheer Chart Attack #3: Christian chart turns 10 | first = Christie | last = Eliezer | work = In Music & Media | archivedate = 18 February 2010 | date = 3 March 2009 | accessdate = 23 December 2015 }}</ref>

